WEBVTT

00:01.697 --> 00:03.525
♪ ♪

00:14.405 --> 00:15.841
[indistinct chatter]

00:15.928 --> 00:17.234
[woman laughs]

00:17.321 --> 00:19.149
Hey! Big dog's here.

00:19.236 --> 00:21.238
-Hey, James.
-Hello!
-What's up?

00:21.325 --> 00:22.457
What's up, how's it going?

00:22.544 --> 00:23.719
Uh, sorry, I just got, you know,

00:23.806 --> 00:25.199
s... uh, stuck at work.

00:25.286 --> 00:26.896
GEORGE:
Yeah, yeah, my boy James here

00:26.983 --> 00:29.507
has an important new job
down at the MIT Media Lab.

00:29.594 --> 00:33.033
Oh! Soon we'll all be working
for James, someday.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.991
WOMAN:
Um, more important:

00:35.078 --> 00:36.210
is he single?

00:36.297 --> 00:38.429
Yes he is.
[chuckles]

00:38.516 --> 00:40.518
And Lucas is, too.
He was just promoted

00:40.605 --> 00:43.826
at his job to manager
at the cell phone store.

00:43.913 --> 00:45.915
Biggest cell phone store
at the mall.

00:46.002 --> 00:47.438
Look, I don't want to brag.

00:47.525 --> 00:51.051
Um, hey, buddy.
You had to work on Thanksgiving?

00:51.138 --> 00:53.705
-Yeah. You know how it is.
-Do I?

00:53.792 --> 00:55.490
No, I guess I'm-I'm surprised

00:55.577 --> 00:57.361
you know, the lab
was open today.

00:57.448 --> 01:00.234
Great. Well, uh, I guess
we can eat now, right?

01:00.321 --> 01:03.454
The prodigal son hath returned.
[chuckles]

01:03.541 --> 01:05.978
Son, hey.
Now, we got to say grace first.

01:06.066 --> 01:07.676
Um, all right, check it out,
everybody,

01:07.763 --> 01:09.634
Annalisa and I are honored
that you, uh, graced us

01:09.721 --> 01:10.896
with your presence.
Now, typically,

01:10.983 --> 01:13.899
I say the grace,
but this year,

01:13.986 --> 01:16.511
my successful second-born son

01:16.598 --> 01:18.469
-will carry on that tradition.
-[Annalisa laughs]

01:18.556 --> 01:20.254
Not that...
Uh, hey, 'cause

01:20.341 --> 01:22.169
-I'm proud of Lucas, too.
I mean, we both are.
-Sure.

01:22.256 --> 01:24.040
-Of course, honey, you're...
-Dad, I-I'm begging you to stop.

01:24.127 --> 01:25.694
-GEORGE: Hey, I see that frown.
-ANNALISA: Yeah.

01:25.781 --> 01:26.869
Turn it upside down.

01:26.956 --> 01:27.826
I'm just saying that, you know,

01:27.913 --> 01:29.176
God has blessed James

01:29.263 --> 01:30.916
-Hallelujah.
-this year with that

01:31.003 --> 01:32.657
new coding job, I just think
he should do the honors.

01:32.744 --> 01:34.877
-ANNALISA: I agree.
-GEORGE: James.

01:34.964 --> 01:36.357
ANNALISA:
James.

01:36.444 --> 01:38.620
James.

01:38.707 --> 01:40.883
Now-now?
Yep, great.

01:40.970 --> 01:43.886
Grace.
Right, grace.

01:43.973 --> 01:45.801
-Okay.
-Everyone, stand. Thank you.

01:45.888 --> 01:47.846
[clears throat]

01:50.719 --> 01:51.981
Stop.

01:53.809 --> 01:56.855
Buddy. Okay.
[short chuckle]

01:56.942 --> 01:59.684
-Jesus. My boy,
-Jesus.

01:59.771 --> 02:01.425
my guy, um...

02:01.512 --> 02:03.862
thank you so much for this,

02:03.949 --> 02:05.516
-you know, this feast of kings.

02:05.603 --> 02:07.083
-Mm, mm, mm.
-Mm!

02:07.170 --> 02:08.476
Y... 'Cause we're kings.

02:08.563 --> 02:09.868
-Yes.
-Each and every one of us.

02:09.955 --> 02:12.088
We're kings.
And, uh, Jesus,

02:12.175 --> 02:13.307
-you know, your shit is...
-[gasps]

02:13.394 --> 02:15.222
-shit.
-You know what? Amen.

02:15.309 --> 02:17.572
-ALL: Amen.
-LUCAS: Can I talk to you
for a second?

02:17.659 --> 02:19.791
-All right. Okay. This way.
-[soft chuckling]

02:19.878 --> 02:20.966
WOMAN:
Amen. [short chuckle]

02:22.925 --> 02:24.231
What are you doing?

02:24.318 --> 02:27.408
Praying.
Sorry for loving the Lord.

02:27.495 --> 02:29.888
-You're drunk.
-You're drunk.

02:29.975 --> 02:33.805
Oh, my God. Like,
I knew you drank, but today?

02:33.892 --> 02:35.720
Thanksgiving,
my favorite holiday,

02:35.807 --> 02:37.113
with all of
our relatives around?

02:37.200 --> 02:40.551
Relax.
I had, uh, dental surgery.

02:40.638 --> 02:42.379
I can see the flask
in your pocket.

02:42.466 --> 02:45.426
I apologize
for being a good time.

02:45.513 --> 02:47.689
Okay, you know what,
you go lie down

02:47.776 --> 02:49.691
and I'll tell them
you're sick, and then

02:49.778 --> 02:52.737
-me and you are gonna talk
when you sober up.
-Oh, my...

02:52.824 --> 02:56.045
No one can tell.
I... [scoffs] Relax.

02:56.132 --> 02:58.134
[short chuckle]
Brother Dad. [laughs]

02:59.309 --> 03:00.397
-Glad you guys like everything.
-Hey.

03:00.484 --> 03:01.790
Hey, every... Oh, sorry.

03:01.877 --> 03:03.357
So lovely, hon.

03:03.444 --> 03:06.098
Hello.
Hey, everybody, hello.

03:06.186 --> 03:09.363
GEORGE:
Dig in. Let's start
with this leg.

03:09.450 --> 03:10.233
He's drunk.

03:10.320 --> 03:11.713
No... Wait.

03:11.800 --> 03:14.194
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no...

03:14.281 --> 03:15.847
That cannot be true.

03:15.934 --> 03:16.979
No one in this family drinks.

03:17.066 --> 03:19.460
LUCAS:
Okay. I am...

03:19.547 --> 03:21.723
-intervening.
-Wait, what?

03:21.810 --> 03:24.029
It's like the-the show--
Intervention,you know?

03:24.116 --> 03:25.030
No, I don't.

03:25.117 --> 03:26.597
LUCAS:
So, on that show,

03:26.684 --> 03:29.731
everyone tells
the person who's drinking

03:29.818 --> 03:30.906
how it's affected their life

03:30.993 --> 03:33.561
and then that person stops.

03:33.648 --> 03:35.345
Hey, James.
Uh,

03:35.432 --> 03:38.130
you drink all the time.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.350
Lucas, James cannot drink
and keep a job like this.

03:40.437 --> 03:41.699
-Mm.
-ANNALISA: Yes...

03:41.786 --> 03:43.397
Lucas.

03:43.484 --> 03:45.137
I mean, look at James--
he's fine,

03:45.225 --> 03:47.357
-He's just a little
tired, you know?
-Yeah.

03:47.444 --> 03:49.098
He's been working really hard
at his new job.

03:49.185 --> 03:51.709
Don't... don't listen to him.
He's...

03:51.796 --> 03:53.276
high.

03:53.363 --> 03:55.670
What?! No, I'm not.
I don't smoke.

03:55.757 --> 03:57.193
-Are you sure?
-I-I'm not...

03:57.280 --> 03:59.108
-JAMES: You smoke so much.
-Look at him!

03:59.195 --> 04:00.762
-He can't even sit up straight.
-[grunting]

04:00.849 --> 04:03.721
-Come on.
-Hey, let's eat.
-ANNALISA: Oh, I love it.

04:03.808 --> 04:05.245
GEORGE:
Why don't we start
by just saying

04:05.332 --> 04:06.985
-what we're thankful for?
-LUCAS: Okay.

04:07.072 --> 04:09.466
I'm thankful that
James didn't die

04:09.553 --> 04:11.294
in that car accident

04:11.381 --> 04:13.035
-where he was drunk driving.
-I'll...

04:13.122 --> 04:14.689
-I'll be-I'll be right back.
-James, James, don't...

04:14.776 --> 04:16.473
-Sit down, James.
-You're not going anywhere.

04:16.560 --> 04:17.692
-I want you to talk to me.
-James, baby, sit back down.

04:17.779 --> 04:19.171
-GEORGE: Hey. Boys.
-George?

04:19.259 --> 04:20.521
-Boys!
-Boys.
-ANNALISA: George.

04:20.608 --> 04:21.565
-Dude.
-Hey, stop!
-Wait...

04:21.652 --> 04:23.088
Get off!

04:28.920 --> 04:31.096
["Uptown Girl" by The Beths
playing]

04:39.104 --> 04:40.149
♪ I feel it happening...♪

04:40.236 --> 04:42.194
Another one?

04:42.282 --> 04:44.066
Yesiree.

04:44.153 --> 04:46.547
Giving you happy hour prices on
that one 'cause of Thanksgiving.

04:46.634 --> 04:49.680
Oh, have I mentioned
that I love you, Ronnie?

04:49.767 --> 04:52.770
-You have, you have.
So many times,
-Mm-hmm.

04:52.857 --> 04:54.555
all right?

04:54.642 --> 04:55.773
♪ I thought
we were friendly...♪

04:55.860 --> 04:58.036
He has arrived.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.214
♪ You had always been someone♪

05:02.302 --> 05:04.826
-♪ I'd take a hit for♪
-[grunting]

05:04.913 --> 05:06.306
Who's this bozo?

05:06.393 --> 05:07.872
I've never seen him
in my life.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.309
JAMES: Nurse.

05:09.396 --> 05:11.223
May I have some
medical assistance,

05:11.311 --> 05:12.747
-please.
-Yes?

05:12.834 --> 05:16.054
-I'll have a piña colada.
-Yeah,

05:16.141 --> 05:17.839
we're not a blender
type of establishment.

05:17.926 --> 05:20.537
Well, then I'll have
a piña colada neat, then.

05:20.624 --> 05:21.973
Okay.

05:22.060 --> 05:24.411
Hey. You want one?

05:24.498 --> 05:25.455
It's on your boy.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.457
A milkshake? No thanks.

05:27.544 --> 05:30.939
Okay. Barkeep, did you know that
this woman hates free things?

05:31.026 --> 05:32.506
Come on, it's not
technically free.

05:32.593 --> 05:34.072
I'd feel like
I owe you something,

05:34.159 --> 05:35.509
like, even a smile,

05:35.596 --> 05:36.510
and I don't
want to do that, so...

05:36.597 --> 05:37.685
[blows raspberry] no.

05:37.772 --> 05:40.209
Ah. Thank you very much.

05:40.296 --> 05:43.995
[exhales]

05:44.082 --> 05:45.997
Oh! My God, that's good.

05:46.084 --> 05:47.999
You, sir-- you got

05:48.086 --> 05:50.480
a great future ahead of you,
did you know that?

05:50.567 --> 05:52.395
-["Pony" by Ginuwine
begins playing]
-Oh!

05:53.396 --> 05:55.529
[laughs, groans]

05:56.573 --> 05:58.009
[muttering, grunting]

06:05.103 --> 06:06.888
[grunts] Yeah.

06:10.282 --> 06:11.893
[laughs]

06:17.420 --> 06:18.639
Yeah. [grunting]

06:18.726 --> 06:20.031
♪ I'm just a bachelor...♪

06:20.118 --> 06:21.729
You got to respect
the commitment,

06:21.816 --> 06:23.861
but I don't want to watch this
anymore. Hey, bud.

06:23.948 --> 06:26.342
Smile, let me buy you a drink.

06:26.429 --> 06:28.431
♪ Who knows how to ride...♪

06:28.518 --> 06:30.607
Let me guess.
Cosmo.

06:30.694 --> 06:32.261
Espresso martini, thank you.

06:32.348 --> 06:34.263
Ugh. Hey, Ronnie,
will you please get a drink

06:34.350 --> 06:35.482
for me and my friend...

06:35.569 --> 06:37.222
-Uh, James.
-...James

06:37.309 --> 06:38.789
here a, uh...
What do you want?

06:38.876 --> 06:41.749
An espresso martini, please.
And thank you...

06:41.836 --> 06:42.837
Oh, Katrina.

06:42.924 --> 06:44.839
Oh, like the hurricane.

06:45.883 --> 06:48.799
Yeah. Well,
happy goddamn Thanksgiving,

06:48.886 --> 06:50.584
-James.
-Uh, y... yeah.

06:50.671 --> 06:53.238
-And to you, good sir.
-Mm-hmm.

06:53.325 --> 06:56.328
♪ Waitin', come and...♪

06:56.416 --> 06:58.722
-Listen.
-What?

06:58.809 --> 07:00.681
Just because
you bought me a drink

07:00.768 --> 07:02.900
doesn't mean that
you can take advantage of me.

07:02.987 --> 07:05.599
What kind of monster
do you think I am?

07:05.686 --> 07:07.949
["Connection" by Elastica
playing]

07:09.080 --> 07:12.301
Oh! Wait, wait, wait.
You're very drunk,

07:12.388 --> 07:14.216
so I just want to make sure
I have your consent.

07:14.303 --> 07:15.173
-Oh, no, you got it.
-Okay.

07:15.260 --> 07:16.740
Do I have yours?

07:16.827 --> 07:17.828
Oh, yeah.
I'm not even that drunk, so...

07:17.915 --> 07:19.787
-Okay.
-[groaning]

07:21.745 --> 07:24.095
Okay, okay, wait.
What if we did, like, a vow?

07:24.182 --> 07:26.968
-You mean like praying?
-No, not like a prayer.

07:27.055 --> 07:28.535
Repeat after me:

07:28.622 --> 07:30.537
I, Katerina,
do consent to one James

07:30.624 --> 07:32.321
in front of God
and everyone here

07:32.408 --> 07:33.714
forever and ever
in perpetuity.

07:33.801 --> 07:35.150
That sounds a lot like
a prayer, man.

07:35.237 --> 07:38.458
Here we go.
I, Katrina, vow to G...

07:38.545 --> 07:41.025
to God and the...
I say yes to the dress. Amen.

07:41.112 --> 07:43.158
Yes.

07:44.855 --> 07:46.422
Onward, Christian soldier.

07:47.162 --> 07:48.206
[chuckles]

07:50.208 --> 07:53.951
-That was fun.
-Oh, yeah. Yeah, it was my
first time doing that, so...

07:54.038 --> 07:55.692
Yeah, yeah, same.
Obviously.

07:55.779 --> 07:57.085
[whispering]: Hey, listen,
I'm gonna go out first.

07:57.172 --> 07:59.783
You have to wait a second
so no one notices.

08:02.786 --> 08:04.266
Ronnie!

08:04.353 --> 08:06.268
This was on the floor
when I got in there.

08:06.355 --> 08:07.748
Can you believe that?
I mean,

08:07.835 --> 08:09.401
you got to tighten up
your shit, man.

08:09.489 --> 08:10.707
-That's embarrassing for you.
-JAMES: Oh, yeah.

08:10.794 --> 08:13.057
No, I-I...
I'll get on those apps

08:13.144 --> 08:14.885
and, uh, code away, man.
I got you.

08:14.972 --> 08:16.887
-Hey.
-Mm.

08:16.974 --> 08:18.062
I thought you went home.

08:18.149 --> 08:19.194
I was looking all over for you.

08:19.281 --> 08:20.456
I'm sorry, Sam, you got to go.

08:20.543 --> 08:21.979
-Huh?
-You have to go.

08:22.066 --> 08:23.372
I have told you multiple times

08:23.459 --> 08:25.069
not to fornicate in my bathroom,
all right?

08:25.156 --> 08:27.115
It violates health code.
Mark

08:27.202 --> 08:28.856
just pissed in a corner.
You got to go.

08:28.943 --> 08:30.988
-No... [sighs]
We were just vaping.
-I have

08:31.075 --> 08:33.121
no idea what
you're talking about.

08:33.208 --> 08:34.601
-God, get out.
-SAMANTHA: You know what?

08:34.688 --> 08:35.732
This is bullshit, Ronnie.

08:35.819 --> 08:36.864
I'm gonna find a new local,

08:36.951 --> 08:39.257
-All right?
-Okay.

08:39.344 --> 08:41.433
-See you tomorrow.
-Yeah, I'll see you
tomorrow, Ron!

08:41.521 --> 08:43.044
[James mumbles]

08:46.177 --> 08:47.570
♪ ♪

08:47.657 --> 08:51.226
Hey, you are
a little liar, Katrina.

08:51.313 --> 08:54.490
Oh, sorry, okay? I didn't want
to be traceable, you know?

08:54.577 --> 08:56.274
I didn't know if you were
a creep. Safety first.

08:56.361 --> 08:58.233
-I still might be a creep.
-Are you?

08:58.320 --> 09:00.452
-Nah.
-Whew.

09:00.540 --> 09:02.019
You know what,

09:02.106 --> 09:04.500
-this is better than a bar.
-Right? Right?

09:04.587 --> 09:07.459
We're outside, we got
fresh air, it's beautiful out.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.679
-I miss the bar.
-Ugh! Me too!

09:09.766 --> 09:12.116
-I miss it so much.
-God, what do people do
on walks?

09:12.203 --> 09:13.683
JAMES:
I hate walking. It's like,

09:13.770 --> 09:15.685
why do you even have to work out
to stay in shape?

09:15.772 --> 09:18.340
Like, why can't I just be fit?

09:18.427 --> 09:21.952
-I just want to
be in shape so bad.
-Yeah. Right. Totally agree.

09:22.039 --> 09:23.954
Uh, we have a lot in common.

09:24.041 --> 09:26.043
Yeah, we really do.

09:27.262 --> 09:28.742
Do you have to
be anywhere, like,

09:28.829 --> 09:30.352
for-for Thanksgiving
or anything like that?

09:30.439 --> 09:32.354
It's not even dark out.
I'm good.

09:32.441 --> 09:34.443
♪ ♪

09:36.488 --> 09:38.752
So, what brought you out
in the first place, anyway?

09:38.839 --> 09:42.538
I am celebrating the great day
I had with my family.

09:42.625 --> 09:44.540
-Mm.
-Doesn't everybody do that?

09:44.627 --> 09:47.108
I have no idea,
I haven't seen my family yet.

09:47.195 --> 09:49.893
I took the train from New York
and went straight to the bar

09:49.980 --> 09:51.591
and I pregamed.

09:51.678 --> 09:54.028
-Always a very good idea
with my mother.
-Yeah.

09:55.464 --> 09:57.205
Do you know what time it is?

10:01.296 --> 10:04.560
-No. Oh.
-Aw. Mm-hmm.

10:04.647 --> 10:07.998
-She is gonna be
so pissed at me.
-Yeah, she is.

10:08.085 --> 10:09.347
She can add it
to the list of things

10:09.434 --> 10:11.349
she's already
mad at me for.

10:11.436 --> 10:13.264
-Ooh!
-If you could make money

10:13.351 --> 10:15.005
from pissing off your parents,
I would

10:15.092 --> 10:17.486
-be very rich.
-Oh.

10:17.573 --> 10:19.662
-You should look into
the chosen family thing.
-Oh, yeah.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.664
Yeah.
That's probably my next move.

10:21.751 --> 10:23.405
Actually, I think
your next move should be

10:23.492 --> 10:26.626
-going home,
because I am a monster.
-Mm. No.

10:26.713 --> 10:28.279
I got kicked out of my family

10:28.366 --> 10:30.847
the day of Thanksgiving.

10:30.934 --> 10:33.545
So, we can be monsters together.

10:34.895 --> 10:36.723
-Okay.
-Mm-hmm.

10:36.810 --> 10:38.855
-[gasps] It's our turn. Yep.
-It's our turn, it's our turn.

10:38.942 --> 10:40.814
Hi, good evening.

10:40.901 --> 10:42.946
I would love
a cheeseburger with fries

10:43.033 --> 10:45.601
and a Coke and a shake
and an ice cream sundae.

10:45.688 --> 10:47.559
Thank you so much.

10:47.647 --> 10:50.127
And I'll have
everything that she had,

10:50.214 --> 10:51.999
but just with,
like, one more.

10:52.086 --> 10:53.522
Respect.

10:53.609 --> 10:55.219
-Right?
-WOMAN: I can't serve you

10:55.306 --> 10:57.178
without a car.

10:57.265 --> 10:59.397
You can't... You...
We-we can't walk up?

10:59.484 --> 11:02.487
-Hence the name "drive-through."
-Never doing it.

11:02.574 --> 11:07.014
Oh, I'm so sorry for the
confusion. We arein a car.

11:07.101 --> 11:09.364
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Yeah, we are. Um,

11:09.451 --> 11:12.323
-turn on the radio, sweetheart.
-Oh, you've got it, honey bear.

11:12.410 --> 11:14.499
-I'd love to turn on the radio.
-Boop, boop.

11:14.586 --> 11:16.371
And the Lord said...
[chuckles]

11:16.458 --> 11:17.894
that Jesus,

11:17.981 --> 11:21.115
[chuckles]
he was, uh, his only son

11:21.202 --> 11:23.291
of me and my wife and...

11:23.378 --> 11:24.335
-SAMANTHA: Different channel.
-They just... Okay.

11:24.422 --> 11:26.381
And this is, uh,

11:26.468 --> 11:29.079
1450 Real Talk radio.

11:29.166 --> 11:30.559
-Ooh.
-[chuckles]

11:30.646 --> 11:32.561
-[chuckles] Vroom, vroom, vroom.
-Vroom, vroom.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.389
Did you get that order, ma'am?

11:35.564 --> 11:37.697
I can literally
see you on the camera.

11:37.784 --> 11:39.655
-I need you to leave right now.
-What?

11:39.742 --> 11:41.701
Don't make me call whoever
you call in this situation.

11:41.788 --> 11:43.398
Okay, ok-okay-- get me...

11:43.485 --> 11:47.054
It's Thanksgiving,
you assholes!

11:50.405 --> 11:54.061
Oh, you are a genius.

11:54.148 --> 11:56.150
["Tu M'as Trop Menti"
by Chantal Goya playing]

12:00.894 --> 12:03.113
[indistinct chatter]

12:03.200 --> 12:04.941
♪ ♪

12:25.179 --> 12:26.658
Was that the best meal
you've ever had?

12:26.746 --> 12:28.399
-Oh, my God, it's a feast.
-Mmm.

12:28.486 --> 12:30.184
-Mmm.
-Oh,

12:30.271 --> 12:32.099
-should we say what
we're thankful for?
-Uh,

12:32.186 --> 12:35.885
okay. I'm thankful I don't
live in this shit town anymore.

12:35.972 --> 12:37.974
Ouch.
I still live here.

12:38.061 --> 12:41.325
Oh, yeah?
Fight me.

12:41.412 --> 12:43.371
No, I got a new job.
It's in coding.

12:43.458 --> 12:46.156
-Sure. Don't know
what that means.
-Doesn't matter,

12:46.243 --> 12:48.158
because I got a big promotion.

12:48.245 --> 12:50.421
-Wow. Congratulations.
-Ah.

12:50.508 --> 12:52.641
And you even like it.
Hot twist.

12:52.728 --> 12:55.513
-I like that I got it, I don't
know if I like doing it yet.
-Ugh.

12:56.558 --> 12:59.126
-Now, that I can get behind.
I hate work.
-Mm.

12:59.213 --> 13:00.736
Okay, no, I don't hate it.

13:00.823 --> 13:02.999
It's just, I got thrown
into the deep end.

13:03.086 --> 13:06.350
It's kinda depressing,
obsessing over this thing,

13:06.437 --> 13:08.396
you know, you go out,
you get it,

13:08.483 --> 13:10.267
and it's too much.

13:11.616 --> 13:13.053
I'm definitely
gonna screw it up.

13:13.140 --> 13:14.968
No, you're not, come on.

13:15.055 --> 13:16.708
It sounds like you just
have imposter syndrome.

13:16.796 --> 13:18.885
Hey, I thought
I had that, but then

13:18.972 --> 13:20.625
it turns out that
I was right about everything

13:20.712 --> 13:22.366
I thought I couldn't do,
which is everything.
-[laughing]

13:22.453 --> 13:23.846
-No way.
-Uh-huh. Seriously,

13:23.933 --> 13:25.979
I get in trouble,
like, all the time.

13:26.066 --> 13:28.808
I feel like a preschooler,
I get scolded a lot. Like,

13:28.895 --> 13:31.462
they're always like,
"You're a mess"

13:31.549 --> 13:33.116
or "you're rude
to your co-workers"

13:33.203 --> 13:35.336
No, no, I don't buy it.

13:35.423 --> 13:38.165
-You're not like that.
-[sighs] Well... no, I know

13:38.252 --> 13:40.036
it seems like I have
my shit together but, like,

13:40.123 --> 13:41.995
I do do those things.

13:42.082 --> 13:44.606
All the time, and I-I honestly,
like, don't even know why.

13:44.693 --> 13:46.956
I think that, um,
I may be just an asshole,

13:47.043 --> 13:48.828
you know, like, genetically.

13:48.915 --> 13:50.612
["13 Jours en France [Choeurs]"
by Francis Lai playing]

13:57.445 --> 13:59.316
That was romantic.

13:59.403 --> 14:00.970
[scoff]
Yeah, well, I'm very romantic.

14:01.057 --> 14:02.754
-Ask anybody.
-[laughs]

14:02.842 --> 14:04.147
-[clears throat]
-Oh.

14:04.234 --> 14:08.369
-Yeah. Are we in Before Sunrise?
-Yeah.

14:08.456 --> 14:10.327
You know what, we could, like,
not exchange info and then

14:10.414 --> 14:13.461
just meet at Good Time Sally's
again next Thanksgiving.

14:13.548 --> 14:14.679
-Yes.
-Yeah.

14:14.766 --> 14:15.985
-I love that idea.
-Mm-hmm.

14:16.072 --> 14:17.552
Maybe we do it every year.

14:17.639 --> 14:19.119
Well, I don't know,
let's see how the rest

14:19.206 --> 14:21.643
of the night goes first.
But, so far, A-plus date.

14:21.730 --> 14:23.340
So this is a date now?

14:23.427 --> 14:25.125
-Yeah.
-Okay.

14:25.212 --> 14:27.170
-It's longer than
most dates I've had.
-Okay.

14:28.955 --> 14:31.740
-JAMES: [whispering]:
What are you doing?
-I got it, it's okay.

14:31.827 --> 14:33.350
[giggles] Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

14:33.437 --> 14:35.265
-Shh, shh.
-Oh... Okay...
-RONNIE: Hey!

14:35.352 --> 14:37.050
-SAMANTHA: What?
-Are you joking
with me right now?

14:37.137 --> 14:38.965
No, no, listen, listen, listen,
I'm only back because

14:39.052 --> 14:41.010
-I forgot my bag.
-As God is my witness,

14:41.097 --> 14:42.707
-she left her bag.
-But hear me out, okay?

14:42.794 --> 14:44.884
'Cause we're already here,
so, like, maybe we just

14:44.971 --> 14:46.798
-have one drink? Come on.
-No.

14:46.886 --> 14:48.191
Oh...

14:48.278 --> 14:50.019
Come here, man.

14:50.106 --> 14:52.630
-Listen, help me out,
please. I mean,
-Please.

14:52.717 --> 14:54.197
this girl's amazing,
and she deserves

14:54.284 --> 14:56.025
a really good Thanksgiving.

14:57.809 --> 15:00.290
-One drink.
-Yes!

15:00.377 --> 15:02.597
RONNIE:
Stay out of the bathroom.

15:02.684 --> 15:04.512
♪ ♪

15:04.599 --> 15:06.644
Yeah, you know, Thanksgiving
used to be fun at my house,

15:06.731 --> 15:08.646
'cause we'd have, like,
a lot of family over

15:08.733 --> 15:11.084
and my mom and I could sit
several seats apart, and it...

15:11.171 --> 15:13.303
it was normal-ish, you know?

15:13.390 --> 15:15.044
I used to call it
"fooling the public."

15:15.131 --> 15:18.265
But now it's just us,
and last year was brutal.

15:18.352 --> 15:20.267
-It was brutal.
-Okay.

15:20.354 --> 15:21.659
But this Thanksgiving--

15:21.746 --> 15:25.228
like, the one I just had today--

15:25.315 --> 15:26.316
-was the worst.
-No, no, no.

15:26.403 --> 15:28.840
Picture my mom-- amom--

15:28.928 --> 15:30.842
sitting up all night,

15:30.930 --> 15:32.714
waiting for me to come home.

15:32.801 --> 15:34.672
That's awful.
That is pretty bad.

15:34.759 --> 15:37.849
-[laughing]: Thank you.
I know, it's so bad.
-It is.

15:37.937 --> 15:40.504
Okay, but my family
probably spent

15:40.591 --> 15:42.332
the entire night
worrying about me.

15:43.551 --> 15:45.509
Why?
You seem so great.

15:45.596 --> 15:46.946
I... I don't know.

15:47.033 --> 15:50.123
My job. My drinking.
Name it.

15:50.210 --> 15:52.734
Yeah, but you've got a great
job, you don't drink that much.

15:52.821 --> 15:54.388
You can't have a job like that
if you're a drunk.

15:54.475 --> 15:56.346
Yeah.

15:56.433 --> 15:58.479
-Uh, maybe.
-Take my word for it.
I've got, like,

15:58.566 --> 16:01.917
a big job, all things
considered, and I'm thriving.

16:02.004 --> 16:05.007
Closing!
You don't have to go home...

16:05.094 --> 16:06.574
-But we can't stay here.
-Oh. Wait.

16:06.661 --> 16:07.705
No.

16:07.792 --> 16:09.969
Oh, yes.

16:10.056 --> 16:12.232
No, come on,
one more drink, Ronnie.

16:12.319 --> 16:14.321
No. First of all,
it's Massachusetts state law,

16:14.408 --> 16:16.105
and secondly,
you've had enough to drink.

16:16.192 --> 16:17.541
[laughs]
Please.

16:17.628 --> 16:19.630
I could drive a school bus.

16:20.762 --> 16:22.764
[coughing, retching]

16:25.506 --> 16:27.595
And that, my friend,

16:27.682 --> 16:30.206
is why I bought the mints
and the...

16:30.293 --> 16:31.686
-the toothbrush. And the gum.
-Mm.

16:31.773 --> 16:32.992
I think you might be, like,

16:33.079 --> 16:34.950
-my personal guru.
-[chuckles]

16:35.037 --> 16:36.691
[coughs]
See, I'd join your cult.

16:36.778 --> 16:39.085
-I would be
such a good cult leader.
-Mm.

16:39.172 --> 16:41.696
No, seriously, I think about it,
like, all the time.

16:41.783 --> 16:44.568
'Cause those things
dissolve into murder

16:44.655 --> 16:46.266
and money laundering,

16:46.353 --> 16:48.311
but it doesn't have to.

16:48.398 --> 16:49.834
Why can't we just

16:49.921 --> 16:52.098
live off the land
and have all the sex?

16:52.185 --> 16:53.795
And it'd be so fun.

16:53.882 --> 16:55.753
All right, we can be
the one good-guy cult,

16:55.840 --> 16:58.104
with all the good
of the cult but without, like,

16:58.191 --> 16:59.540
the legal mess and whatnot.

16:59.627 --> 17:01.324
-Yeah, yeah.
-I'm 100% in and I think

17:01.411 --> 17:03.674
-we would make bank.
-[laughs]

17:03.761 --> 17:06.373
Okay, so what's next?
Maybe we go to Fenway.

17:06.460 --> 17:08.418
-Break in there?
-Uh-uh. I'm getting tired.

17:08.505 --> 17:10.855
-Or, like, a roller skate
or something like...
-Okay, hang on a second.

17:10.942 --> 17:13.162
I think you're trying to
trick me into exercise again.

17:13.249 --> 17:14.903
Oh, ha. Gross.

17:14.990 --> 17:16.383
I didn't even mean to.

17:18.037 --> 17:19.777
Oh, God, it's so late.

17:19.864 --> 17:22.780
Uh, actually,
I kinda think that, like...

17:22.867 --> 17:24.173
I should go home.

17:24.260 --> 17:26.132
Oh, no. No way.
Come o... We...

17:26.219 --> 17:27.481
It's not even light out.

17:27.568 --> 17:29.526
Right?
Like, we just got here.

17:29.613 --> 17:31.398
-Come...
-Where?

17:31.485 --> 17:32.529
Right here. Y...

17:32.616 --> 17:33.878
Where we're, uh, standing.

17:33.965 --> 17:36.055
Uh... [sighs]

17:36.142 --> 17:37.839
Uh, come on, come on, come on.
We've had such a great night.

17:37.926 --> 17:39.232
Like, it can't end here.

17:39.319 --> 17:41.060
I don't... I don't know.

17:41.147 --> 17:43.018
Please, please.
I really...

17:43.105 --> 17:44.802
I can't go home.

17:48.110 --> 17:51.070
I know-- what if we just
walked into the street,

17:51.157 --> 17:52.897
waited for a car to come,

17:52.984 --> 17:54.551
and then just got out of the way
right before it came?

17:54.638 --> 17:57.206
-Yeah. Yeah. For real,
-Like in The Notebook.

17:57.293 --> 17:59.513
can you imagine?
-Yeah. Yeah. Come on,
it'll be fun.

17:59.600 --> 18:01.863
No, dude, that's, like,
a really bad idea, okay?

18:01.950 --> 18:03.865
-No, no. You're being
-Why don't we do something like

18:03.952 --> 18:04.953
-a spoilsport.
-jump off a bridge?

18:05.040 --> 18:06.215
[car honking]

18:06.302 --> 18:07.564
Dude, dude!

18:07.651 --> 18:10.524
[grunts]
What are you doing?!

18:10.611 --> 18:12.961
-What is wrong with you?
-You don't want to try it?

18:13.048 --> 18:15.137
No, I don't want to try it.
I don't have a death wish.

18:16.225 --> 18:17.487
-I-It's not like that.
-That was insane.

18:17.574 --> 18:19.402
Do you know how insane that is?

18:21.970 --> 18:23.928
No, I don't...

18:24.015 --> 18:25.408
I-I don't even know.

18:26.931 --> 18:28.759
-Okay.
-Uh...

18:29.804 --> 18:32.328
I'm sorry.
We were having such a nice time,

18:32.415 --> 18:33.503
-Yeah, it's okay.
-that...

18:33.590 --> 18:36.027
No, it really isn't.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.161
No, it's not, actually.

18:39.248 --> 18:41.685
That was messed-up, man.
You need help.

18:41.772 --> 18:43.209
I don't know, you should,
like, talk to somebody--

18:43.296 --> 18:45.080
a therapist or...

18:45.167 --> 18:47.387
I don't know, people are always
saying that to me, but I'm fine.

18:47.474 --> 18:50.738
My family doesn't really
believe in therapy.

18:51.782 --> 18:53.001
They might if they
knew the alternative.

18:53.088 --> 18:54.829
Sorry, I just feel like

18:54.916 --> 18:56.439
you need something.

18:56.526 --> 18:57.875
Yeah.

19:00.182 --> 19:01.749
You should go.

19:01.836 --> 19:03.794
Yeah.
I'm s-so sorry.

19:03.881 --> 19:05.274
-No, please. Don't be.
-Yeah.

19:05.361 --> 19:07.407
You know, I-I had
so much fun tonight,

19:07.494 --> 19:09.887
except for this whole end bit,
which was terrible.

19:09.974 --> 19:12.020
♪ ♪

19:12.107 --> 19:15.066
-Uh...
-Yeah.

19:22.813 --> 19:24.163
I'll see you at the bar
in one year's time.

19:24.250 --> 19:25.642
Yeah, I'll see you then.

19:32.606 --> 19:34.608
[indistinct chatter]

19:41.615 --> 19:42.877
LUCAS:
Yo, bro.

19:42.964 --> 19:44.705
Yo.
Thanks for coming out, man.

19:44.792 --> 19:46.359
I don't know how to do this.

19:46.446 --> 19:48.709
Hey, man,
baby steps and all that.

19:48.796 --> 19:51.059
Besides, if we don't like it,
we just leave.

19:51.146 --> 19:53.540
[chuckles]
Y-Yeah.

19:53.627 --> 19:55.542
But you can't leave
in the middle.

19:55.629 --> 19:58.414
Yes, you can.
Do you see guards or anything?

19:58.501 --> 20:01.112
Yeah. There are so many guards.
Like, look at her.

20:01.200 --> 20:03.680
-Hi, good to see you.
-LUCAS: Here's my question.
Like,

20:03.767 --> 20:06.727
did you have to dress
like an alcoholic, though?

20:06.814 --> 20:08.119
-I don't like this on you.
-It happens.

20:08.207 --> 20:09.947
I love it.
You bought it for me.

20:10.034 --> 20:11.601
LUCAS:
I realize now it just
makes you look like

20:11.688 --> 20:14.082
-a giant fourth-grader.
-Best year of my life.

20:14.169 --> 20:15.997
-But, like, a fourth-grader
who's good at math.
-OLIVIA: Good. Hey, what's up?

20:16.084 --> 20:17.825
I'm sorry.

20:17.912 --> 20:19.783
Hi. I'm Olivia.

20:19.870 --> 20:21.611
First time?

20:21.698 --> 20:23.178
Yeah.

20:24.179 --> 20:26.050
Welcome.

20:26.137 --> 20:27.356
There's snacks.

20:27.443 --> 20:29.924
♪ ♪

20:30.011 --> 20:32.492
There's snacks. Come on.

20:32.579 --> 20:34.929
Gushers, Cheez-Its,
little, uh...

20:35.016 --> 20:37.888
-JAMES: Peanut butter
sandwich things.
-LUCAS: Oh, I do love those.
